    <button class="back-btn" onclick="window.history.back()">Back</button>

    <div class="content-wrapper">
        <h1 class="about-title">About Us</h1>
        
        <p class="about-intro">This page explains what our business does and why incorporating blockchain brings extra advantages to businesses that use our platform.</p>

        <div class="about-section">
            <h3>Details about the business</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Business model:</strong> LegiLah is a Carousel-style online marketplace where users can buy and sell second-hand or brand-new items.</li>
                <li><strong>Target users:</strong> Everyday buyers, casual sellers, and small businesses that want a safer and more transparent platform to sell their products.</li>
                <li><strong>Core features:</strong> Product listings, chat between buyer and seller, shopping and delivery tracking, and seller rating and reputation.</li>
                <li><strong>Pain points we address:</strong> Fraud, manipulated ratings, unclear delivery status, and off-platform payments that are hard to verify.</li>
                <li><strong>Value proposition:</strong> We keep the familiar feel of existing platforms (like Carousel) but add an extra layer of trust and transparency using blockchain.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="about-section">
            <h3>Advantages of incorporating blockchain into your business</h3>
            <p>When businesses and sellers use a blockchain-backed marketplace like LegiLah, they gain extra benefits that traditional platforms cannot easily provide.</p>
            <div class="benefits-grid">
                <div class="benefit-item">
                    <strong>Tamper-resistant records</strong>
                    Orders, ratings, and key delivery updates can be recorded in a way that is difficult to secretly change or delete.
                </div>
                <div class="benefit-item">
                    <strong>Stronger reputation</strong>
                    Seller rating and history become more reliable because they are based on verified transactions instead of easily faked records.
                </div>
                <div class="benefit-item">
                    <strong>Clearer audit trail</strong>
                    Businesses can see a transparent history of transactions, which helps during disputes, refunds, or internal checks.
                </div>
                <div class="benefit-item">
                    <strong>Improved operations</strong>
                    Shopping and delivery status can be shared across buyers, sellers, and logistics partners with a single, trusted source of truth.
                </div>
                <div class="benefit-item">
                    <strong>Higher customer confidence</strong>
                    Customers are more likely to buy when they can see consistent on-chain history and trustworthy seller ratings.
                </div>
                <div class="benefit-item">
                    <strong>Reduced fraud risk</strong>
                    By keeping key information on-chain instead of only in private chats or screenshots, it is harder for bad actors to cheat the system.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-section">
            <h3>How we apply blockchain in LegiLah</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>We use a Proof of Stake (PoS) style blockchain, which is faster and more energy-efficient than traditional Proof of Work.</li>
                <li>The chain supports smart contracts, allowing automated logic for updating ratings, recording delivery events, and managing transaction data.</li>
                <li>This design gives businesses a balance of security, speed, and transparency suitable for a modern marketplace.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
